The paper deals with characterizing the degrees of freedom of interference channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the use of subspaces and interference alignment, which are concepts in network information theory (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also covers multiple-input multiple-output channels (cs.MM) and complex vector channels (cs.CC).
